CONDITIONS OF USE FOR MOBILE TICKETING SERVICE\10To buy a ticket, the app sends a request by SMS to the ATAF Mobile Ticketing system (visit the ataf website for more details). The ticket price (€ 1.80 per 90 minutes) is in addition to the cost of the SMS, which varies according to your operator. The service is available for customers of Italian operators: TIM, VODAFONE, WINDTRE. You will receive a message shortly after containing the details of the electronic ticket, the time of issue and period of validity. The ticket is stamped on purchase, and does not therefore require any additional validation. If asked to show your ticket on board, just show the controller the code you received by SMS.\10After sending the request SMS, you can find the text containing the details of the e-ticket with the code to show the ticket controller on board in your SMS inbox on your mobile phone (not in the ATAF app). Before boarding, make sure you have received an e-ticket SMS valid for the period of your journey. If you do not receive the SMS with the ticket details, check that the request SMS was sent correctly in sent messages on your mobile phone.\10ATAF GESTIONI SRL and the provider of technologies, MOOVIT APP GLOBAL LTD, are not liable to third parties for direct or indirect damage caused by not being able to buy an e-ticket from the ATAF app due to causes not dependent on the app, such as: insufficient calling credit, no connection, failed transaction on the Mobile Ticketing system, failure to receive the SMS, other issues with the telecommunications provider, Mobile Ticketing platform, communications infrastructure between architecture hubs, etc.
